As the floods continue across the Lowveld, roads in the Kruger National Park are still affected. The latest update from the park said the Letaba low-water bridge on the H14 is flooding and closed. The S112 and S114 are also closed and in need of repairs before tourists can make use of them again. ALSO READ: Nationwide floods classified as national disaster The H1-1 De la Porte road also washed away. This means there is no access on the main road between Skukuza and Malelane/Berg en Dal/Jock Safari Lodge or Pretoriuskop. The park said an update regarding more developments will be posted as soon as it is received.